                    ignoreLuxury: !1
                });

            }

                return this.searchUriObject.generateSortingUrls()

            key: "hasGPS",
            value: function() {

                return {
                    url: e.getUrl({
                        filterData: this.msp.filter
                    }),
                    searchName: this.savedName(e.getCurrentFactory(), this.msp)
                }
            },
            savedName: function(e, t) {
                var a = []
                  , i = {
                    min: t.filter.minPrice,
                    max: t.filter.maxPrice
                }
                  , o = {
                    min: t.filter.beds
                }
                  , n = {
                    min: t.filter.baths
                }
                  , l = t.filter.propertyType
                  , d = this.glb.seo.h1;

                i && i.min && i.max)
                    if ("0" !== i.min && "0" === i.max)
                        a.push("$" + s.a.friendlyPrice(i.min));
                    else {
                        var c = "0" === i.min ? i.min : "$" + s.a.friendlyPrice(i.min);
                        a.push(c + "-$" + s.a.friendlyPrice(i.max))
                    }
                return o && o.min && a.push(o.min + "+ Beds"),
                n && n.min && a.push(n.min + "+ Baths"),
                "string" != typeof l && l.length && (l = l.map(function(e) {
                    return r.propertyTypeDataMap[e]
                }),
                a.push(l.join(", "))),
                a.join(", ")
            },
            actionSaveSearch: function() {

                  , t = this;

                    },

                })
            },

                })
            },
            handleAddSaveSearchByEmail: function(e) {

                  , a = n({
                    email: e.user.email,

                }, this.getBaseDataForSaveSearch());

                    t.$eventBus.$emit("call-finish", !0)

            },
            addEventListenerForSaveSearchLite: function() {
                var e = this;
                this.$eventBus.$on("call-savesearch", function(t) {
                    t.byEmail ? e.handleAddSaveSearchByEmail(t) : e.handleDefaultAddSaveSearch(t)
                })
            }

                },

                }
            },

                    return this.searchText.length > this.delayLoad ? this.suggestLinkList : this.defaultSuggestLinkList
                }

                },

                    },

                    }

            }),
            mounted: function() {
                var t = this;
                e(document).on("click.autocomplete" + this._uid, function() {
                    e(document).trigger("dom.automplete.hide" + t._uid)
                }),

                        }),

                            if ("ArrowLeft" !== a.key && "ArrowRight" !== a.key)
                                return "ArrowDown" === a.key ? t.next() : "ArrowUp" === a.key ? t.prev() : "Escape" === a.key ? t.hide() : "Enter" === a.key ? (document.activeElement && document.activeElement.blur(),

                                t.hide()) : void 0

            },
            methods: n({}, Object(r.b)("glb", ["getAutoSuggestSavedSearch"]), Object(r.d)("glb", ["updateSubscriptions"]), {

                    case "removeNotification":

                    }
                },
                action: function(e) {
                    switch (e.action) {
                    case "geoSearch":
                        this.geoSearch();

                    case "redirect":
                        this.redirectTo(e.url);
                        break;
                    case "searchBySuggestion":

                    }

                    this.index = -1,

                },
                recordTolinks: function() {

                        return e.zipcode - t.zipcode
                    }),
                    t.reduce(function(t, a) {
                        if (a.disabled)
                            return t;
                        var i = ""
                          , o = ""
                          , r = ""

        t.prototype.changeSlide = function(t, a) {
            var i = this, o = e(t.currentTarget), r, s, n;
            switch (o.is("a") && t.preventDefault(),
            o.is("li") || (o = o.closest("li")),
            n = 0 != i.slideCount % i.options.slidesToScroll,
            r = n ? 0 : (i.slideCount - i.currentSlide) % i.options.slidesToScroll,
            t.data.message) {
            case "previous":
                s = 0 === r ? i.options.slidesToScroll : i.options.slidesToShow - r,
                i.slideCount > i.options.slidesToShow && i.slideHandler(i.currentSlide - s, !1, a);
                break;
            case "next":
                s = 0 === r ? i.options.slidesToScroll : r,
                i.slideCount > i.options.slidesToShow && i.slideHandler(i.currentSlide + s, !1, a);
                break;
            case "index":
                var l = 0 === t.data.index ? 0 : t.data.index || o.index() * i.options.slidesToScroll;
                i.slideHandler(i.checkNavigable(l), !1, a),
                o.children().trigger("focus");
                break;
            default:
            }
        }

        t.prototype.checkNavigable = function(e) {
            var t = this, a, i;
            if (a = t.getNavigableIndexes(),
            i = 0,
            e > a[a.length - 1])
                e = a[a.length - 1];
            else
                for (var o in a) {
                    if (e < a[o]) {
                        e = i;
                        break
                    }
                    i = a[o]
                }
            return e
        }

        t.prototype.destroy = function(t) {

        t.prototype.getDotCount = function() {
            var e = this
              , t = 0
              , a = 0
              , i = 0;
            if (!0 === e.options.infinite) {
                if (e.slideCount <= e.options.slidesToShow)
                    ++i;
                else
                    for (; t < e.slideCount; )
                        ++i,
                        t = a + e.options.slidesToScroll,
                        a += e.options.slidesToScroll <= e.options.slidesToShow ? e.options.slidesToScroll : e.options.slidesToShow;
            } else if (!0 === e.options.centerMode)
                i = e.slideCount;
            else if (!e.options.asNavFor)
                i = 1 + o((e.slideCount - e.options.slidesToShow) / e.options.slidesToScroll);

                for (; t < e.slideCount; )
                    ++i,
                    t = a + e.options.slidesToScroll,

        }

        t.prototype.getLeft = function(e) {
            var t = this, a = 0, i, o, s, n;
            return t.slideOffset = 0,
            o = t.$slides.first().outerHeight(!0),
            !0 === t.options.infinite ? (t.slideCount > t.options.slidesToShow && (t.slideOffset = -1 * (t.slideWidth * t.options.slidesToShow),
            n = -1,
            !0 === t.options.vertical && !0 === t.options.centerMode && (2 === t.options.slidesToShow ? n = -1.5 : 1 === t.options.slidesToShow && (n = -2)),
            a = o * t.options.slidesToShow * n),
            0 != t.slideCount % t.options.slidesToScroll && e + t.options.slidesToScroll > t.slideCount && t.slideCount > t.options.slidesToShow && (e > t.slideCount ? (t.slideOffset = -1 * ((t.options.slidesToShow - (e - t.slideCount)) * t.slideWidth),
            a = -1 * ((t.options.slidesToShow - (e - t.slideCount)) * o)) : (t.slideOffset = -1 * (t.slideCount % t.options.slidesToScroll * t.slideWidth),
            a = -1 * (t.slideCount % t.options.slidesToScroll * o)))) : e + t.options.slidesToShow > t.slideCount && (t.slideOffset = (e + t.options.slidesToShow - t.slideCount) * t.slideWidth,
            a = (e + t.options.slidesToShow - t.slideCount) * o),
            t.slideCount <= t.options.slidesToShow && (t.slideOffset = 0,
            a = 0),
            !0 === t.options.centerMode && t.slideCount <= t.options.slidesToShow ? t.slideOffset = t.slideWidth * r(t.options.slidesToShow) / 2 - t.slideWidth * t.slideCount / 2 : !0 === t.options.centerMode && !0 === t.options.infinite ? t.slideOffset += t.slideWidth * r(t.options.slidesToShow / 2) - t.slideWidth : !0 === t.options.centerMode && (t.slideOffset = 0,
            t.slideOffset += t.slideWidth * r(t.options.slidesToShow / 2)),
            i = !1 === t.options.vertical ? -1 * (e * t.slideWidth) + t.slideOffset : -1 * (e * o) + a,
            !0 === t.options.variableWidth && (s = t.slideCount <= t.options.slidesToShow || !1 === t.options.infinite ? t.$slideTrack.children(".slick-slide").eq(e) : t.$slideTrack.children(".slick-slide").eq(e + t.options.slidesToShow),
            i = !0 === t.options.rtl ? s[0] ? -1 * (t.$slideTrack.width() - s[0].offsetLeft - s.width()) : 0 : s[0] ? -1 * s[0].offsetLeft : 0,

            i += (t.$list.width() - s.outerWidth()) / 2)),
            i
        }

        }

                i.push(t),

            return i
        }

        }

                    !1

        }

        t.prototype.init = function(t) {

        }

        t.prototype.initADA = function() {
            var t = this
              , a = o(t.slideCount / t.options.slidesToShow)
              , r = t.getNavigableIndexes().filter(function(e) {
                return 0 <= e && e < t.slideCount
            });
            t.$slides.add(t.$slideTrack.find(".slick-cloned")).attr({
                "aria-hidden": "true",
                tabindex: "-1"
            }).find("a, input, button, select").attr({
                tabindex: "-1"
            }),
            null !== t.$dots && (t.$slides.not(t.$slideTrack.find(".slick-cloned")).each(function(a) {
                var i = r.indexOf(a);
                if (e(this).attr({
                    role: "tabpanel",
                    id: "slick-slide" + t.instanceUid + a,
                    tabindex: -1
                }),
                -1 !== i) {
                    var o = "slick-slide-control" + t.instanceUid + i;
                    e("#" + o).length && e(this).attr({
                        "aria-describedby": o
                    })
                }
            }),
            t.$dots.attr("role", "tablist").find("li").each(function(o) {
                var i = r[o];
                e(this).attr({
                    role: "presentation"
                }),
                e(this).find("button").first().attr({
                    role: "tab",
                    id: "slick-slide-control" + t.instanceUid + o,
                    "aria-controls": "slick-slide" + t.instanceUid + i,
                    "aria-label": o + 1 + " of " + a,
                    "aria-selected": null,
                    tabindex: "-1"
                })
            }).eq(t.currentSlide).find("button").attr({
                "aria-selected": "true",
                tabindex: "0"
            }).end());
            for (var s = t.currentSlide, i = s + t.options.slidesToShow; s < i; s++)
                t.options.focusOnChange ? t.$slides.eq(s).attr({
                    tabindex: "0"
                }) : t.$slides.eq(s).removeAttr("tabindex");
            t.activateADA()
        }

        t.prototype.initArrowEvents = function() {
            var e = this;
            !0 === e.options.arrows && e.slideCount > e.options.slidesToShow && (e.$prevArrow.off("click.slick").on("click.slick", {

        }

        }

        t.prototype.initUI = function() {

            !0 === e.options.arrows && e.slideCount > e.options.slidesToShow && (e.$prevArrow.show(),
            e.$nextArrow.show()),
            !0 === e.options.dots && e.slideCount > e.options.slidesToShow && e.$dots.show()
        }
        ,
        t.prototype.keyHandler = function(e) {
            var t = this;
            e.target.tagName.match("TEXTAREA|INPUT|SELECT") || (37 === e.keyCode && !0 === t.options.accessibility ? t.changeSlide({
                data: {
                    message: !0 === t.options.rtl ? "next" : "previous"
                }
            }) : 39 === e.keyCode && !0 === t.options.accessibility && t.changeSlide({
                data: {
                    message: !0 === t.options.rtl ? "previous" : "next"
                }
            }))
        }

        t.prototype.lazyLoad = function() {
            function t(t) {
                e("img[data-lazy]", t).each(function() {
                    var t = e(this)
                      , i = e(this).attr("data-lazy")
                      , o = e(this).attr("data-srcset")
                      , r = e(this).attr("data-sizes") || a.$slider.attr("data-sizes")
                      , s = document.createElement("img");
                    s.onload = function() {
                        t.animate({
                            opacity: 0
                        }, 100, function() {
                            o && (t.attr("srcset", o),
                            r && t.attr("sizes", r)),
                            t.attr("src", i).animate({
                                opacity: 1
                            }, 200, function() {
                                t.removeAttr("data-lazy data-srcset data-sizes").removeClass("slick-loading")
                            }),
                            a.$slider.trigger("lazyLoaded", [a, t, i])
                        })
                    }
                    ,
                    s.onerror = function() {
                        t.removeAttr("data-lazy").removeClass("slick-loading").addClass("slick-lazyload-error"),
                        a.$slider.trigger("lazyLoadError", [a, t, i])
                    }
                    ,
                    s.src = i
                })
            }
            var a = this, r, s, n, l;
            if (!0 === a.options.centerMode ? !0 === a.options.infinite ? (n = a.currentSlide + (a.options.slidesToShow / 2 + 1),
            l = n + a.options.slidesToShow + 2) : (n = Math.max(0, a.currentSlide - (a.options.slidesToShow / 2 + 1)),
            l = 2 + (a.options.slidesToShow / 2 + 1) + a.currentSlide) : (n = a.options.infinite ? a.options.slidesToShow + a.currentSlide : a.currentSlide,
            l = o(n + a.options.slidesToShow),
            !0 === a.options.fade && (0 < n && n--,
            l <= a.slideCount && l++)),
            r = a.$slider.find(".slick-slide").slice(n, l),
            "anticipated" === a.options.lazyLoad)
                for (var d = n - 1, c = l, p = a.$slider.find(".slick-slide"), h = 0; h < a.options.slidesToScroll; h++)
                    0 > d && (d = a.slideCount - 1),
                    r = r.add(p.eq(d)),
                    r = r.add(p.eq(c)),
                    d--,
                    c++;
            t(r),
            a.slideCount <= a.options.slidesToShow ? (s = a.$slider.find(".slick-slide"),
            t(s)) : a.currentSlide >= a.slideCount - a.options.slidesToShow ? (s = a.$slider.find(".slick-cloned").slice(0, a.options.slidesToShow),
            t(s)) : 0 === a.currentSlide && (s = a.$slider.find(".slick-cloned").slice(-1 * a.options.slidesToShow),
            t(s))
        }
        ,

        t.prototype.progressiveLazyLoad = function(t) {
            t = t || 1;
            var a = this, i = e("img[data-lazy]", a.$slider), o, r, s, n, l;
            i.length ? (o = i.first(),
            r = o.attr("data-lazy"),

                a.progressiveLazyLoad()
            }
            ,
            l.onerror = function() {
                3 > t ? setTimeout(function() {
                    a.progressiveLazyLoad(t + 1)
                }, 500) : (o.removeAttr("data-lazy").removeClass("slick-loading").addClass("slick-lazyload-error"),
                a.$slider.trigger("lazyLoadError", [a, o, r]),
                a.progressiveLazyLoad())
            }
            ,
            l.src = r) : a.$slider.trigger("allImagesLoaded", [a])
        }
        ,
        t.prototype.refresh = function(t) {
            var a = this, i, o;
            o = a.slideCount - a.options.slidesToShow,
            !a.options.infinite && a.currentSlide > o && (a.currentSlide = o),
            a.slideCount <= a.options.slidesToShow && (a.currentSlide = 0),

            }),
            a.init(),
            t || a.changeSlide({
                data: {
                    message: "index",
                    index: i
                }
            }, !1)
        }

        t.prototype.registerBreakpoints = function() {
            var t = this, a = t.options.responsive || null, i, o, r;
            if ("array" === e.type(a) && a.length) {
                for (i in t.respondTo = t.options.respondTo || "window",
                a)
                    if (r = t.breakpoints.length - 1,
                    a.hasOwnProperty(i)) {
                        for (o = a[i].breakpoint; 0 <= r; )
                            t.breakpoints[r] && t.breakpoints[r] === o && t.breakpoints.splice(r, 1),
                            r--;
                        t.breakpoints.push(o),
                        t.breakpointSettings[o] = a[i].settings
                    }
                t.breakpoints.sort(function(e, a) {
                    return t.options.mobileFirst ? e - a : a - e
                })
            }
        }

        t.prototype.reinit = function() {
            var t = this;
            t.$slides = t.$slideTrack.children(t.options.slide).addClass("slick-slide"),
            t.slideCount = t.$slides.length,
            t.currentSlide >= t.slideCount && 0 !== t.currentSlide && (t.currentSlide -= t.options.slidesToScroll),
            t.slideCount <= t.options.slidesToShow && (t.currentSlide = 0),

        t.prototype.removeSlide = t.prototype.slickRemove = function(e, t, a) {
            var i = this;
            return "boolean" == typeof e ? (t = e,
            e = !0 === t ? 0 : i.slideCount - 1) : e = !0 === t ? --e : e,
            !(1 > i.slideCount || 0 > e || e > i.slideCount - 1) && void (i.unload(),

        t.prototype.setCSS = function(e) {

        }

        t.prototype.setFade = function() {
            var t = this, a;
            t.$slides.each(function(i, o) {
                a = -1 * (t.slideWidth * i),
                !0 === t.options.rtl ? e(o).css({
                    position: "relative",
                    right: a,
                    top: 0,
                    zIndex: t.options.zIndex - 2,
                    opacity: 0
                }) : e(o).css({

                    left: a,
                    top: 0,

                    opacity: 0
                })
            }),
            t.$slides.eq(t.currentSlide).css({
                zIndex: t.options.zIndex - 1,
                opacity: 1
            })
        }

            var e = this;

                var t = e.$slides.eq(e.currentSlide).outerHeight(!0);
                e.$list.css("height", t)
            }
        }
        ,
        t.prototype.setOption = t.prototype.slickSetOption = function() {
            var t = this, a = !1, i, o, r, s, n;
            if ("object" === e.type(arguments[0]) ? (r = arguments[0],
            a = arguments[1],
            n = "multiple") : "string" === e.type(arguments[0]) && (r = arguments[0],
            s = arguments[1],
            a = arguments[2],
            "responsive" === arguments[0] && "array" === e.type(arguments[1]) ? n = "responsive" : "undefined" != typeof arguments[1] && (n = "single")),
            "single" === n)
                t.options[r] = s;
            else if ("multiple" === n)
                e.each(r, function(e, a) {
                    t.options[e] = a
                });
            else if ("responsive" === n)
                for (o in s)
                    if ("array" !== e.type(t.options.responsive))
                        t.options.responsive = [s[o]];
                    else {
                        for (i = t.options.responsive.length - 1; 0 <= i; )
                            t.options.responsive[i].breakpoint === s[o].breakpoint && t.options.responsive.splice(i, 1),
                            i--;
                        t.options.responsive.push(s[o])
                    }
            a && (t.unload(),
            t.reinit())
        }
        ,
        t.prototype.setPosition = function() {
            var e = this;
            e.setDimensions(),
            e.setHeight(),
            !1 === e.options.fade ? e.setCSS(e.getLeft(e.currentSlide)) : e.setFade(),
            e.$slider.trigger("setPosition", [e])
        }
        ,
        t.prototype.setProps = function() {
            var e = this
              , t = document.body.style;
            e.positionProp = !0 === e.options.vertical ? "top" : "left",
            "top" === e.positionProp ? e.$slider.addClass("slick-vertical") : e.$slider.removeClass("slick-vertical"),
            (t.WebkitTransition !== void 0 || t.MozTransition !== void 0 || t.msTransition !== void 0) && !0 === e.options.useCSS && (e.cssTransitions = !0),
            e.options.fade && ("number" == typeof e.options.zIndex ? 3 > e.options.zIndex && (e.options.zIndex = 3) : e.options.zIndex = e.defaults.zIndex),
            t.OTransform !== void 0 && (e.animType = "OTransform",
            e.transformType = "-o-transform",
            e.transitionType = "OTransition",
            t.perspectiveProperty === void 0 && t.webkitPerspective === void 0 && (e.animType = !1)),
            t.MozTransform !== void 0 && (e.animType = "MozTransform",
            e.transformType = "-moz-transform",
            e.transitionType = "MozTransition",
            t.perspectiveProperty === void 0 && t.MozPerspective === void 0 && (e.animType = !1)),
            t.webkitTransform !== void 0 && (e.animType = "webkitTransform",
            e.transformType = "-webkit-transform",
            e.transitionType = "webkitTransition",
            t.perspectiveProperty === void 0 && t.webkitPerspective === void 0 && (e.animType = !1)),
            t.msTransform !== void 0 && (e.animType = "msTransform",
            e.transformType = "-ms-transform",
            e.transitionType = "msTransition",
            t.msTransform === void 0 && (e.animType = !1)),

        ,
        t.prototype.swipeDirection = function() {

            return t = e.touchObject.startX - e.touchObject.curX,
            o = e.touchObject.startY - e.touchObject.curY,

        }
        ,
        t.prototype.swipeEnd = function() {
            var e = this, t, a;
            if (e.dragging = !1,
            e.swiping = !1,
            e.scrolling)

                !1;

        t.prototype.swipeHandler = function(e) {

        "san-francisco-ca": "<p id=\"safest\"><b>What's it like to live in San Francisco?</b></p><p>Considered by many to be one of the most beautiful cities in the world, San Francisco is a historical American city that could be compared to the New York City of the West Coast. While it doesn't have as many skyscrapers as Manhattan or the sheer size of population, the numerous bridges spanning the Bay, the fog that rolls in on a daily basis and the Northern California micro-climate make San Francisco one of the more unique cities in the world. The main city itself spans a peninsula and as long as you don't mind negotiating a few very steep hills in the middle of it, it is relatively easy to walk over the course of a day. There are numerous different districts to visit, from Chinatown to <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/15/haight-ashbury-in-the-1960s_n_1967664.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">Haight-Ashbury </a>to the Embarcadero, all of which have their own unique histories, subcultures and offer numerous different things to do.</p> <p ><b>What are some things to do in San Francisco? </b></p><p>How much time do you have? Even locals who have lived in San Francisco for decades are discovering new things about their own city. For the newcomers, start big and then discover the cultural subtleties as you blend in with your fellow San Franciscans. Grab a romantic Italian dinner in North Beach and catch a baseball game at the magnificent Pac Bell Park, home of the multi-World Series Champions San Francisco Giants. Shop and hit some dive bars in Haight-Ashbury or spend a day wandering through Golden Gate Park, from the Science or <a href=\"http://deyoung.famsf.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">De Young Museum</a> to the <a href=\"http://www.sfbotanicalgarden.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">Botanical Gardens</a> to the Polo Fields, ending at the beach along the Pacific. Grab great Asian food in Chinatown or explore the newly revived areas of Dogpatch, thanks to the tech industry moving their offices into the areas. That alone will fill a weekend and you'll have barely scratched the surface.</p> <p ><b>Why you'll love it here</b></p><p>If a city could be a mosaic of everything fascinating about the West Coast of America, San Francisco would be it. The landscape is literally shifting beneath your feet and offers beauty in everything from its views to its foliage pretty much no matter where you look. The climate is never too hot nor too cold and that allows the city to keep on humming, almost year-round. With the long history from the days of the California Gold Rush that helped build San Francisco to the modern tech revolution that has made it one of the most important cities in the world today, there's a sense that the city by the Bay is a special place to be when you live there and you wouldn't rather be anywhere else.</p>",
        "houston-tx": "<p id=\"safest\"><b>What's it like to live in Houston, Texas?</b></p><p >Houston, Texas is the fourth largest city in the United States. The sprawling community resides by the Texas Gulf Coast and is considered one of the most ethnically and religiously diverse cities in North America. The character of its neighborhoods, from the gleaming skyscrapers of downtown, to the quirkiness of Montrose, the antique charm of the Heights, or the modern air of the city's various suburbs, reflects that diversity.</p><p >The cost of living in Houston is about 10 percent below the national average. Salaries in the city's various industries, including energy, aerospace, biotech, and health care, are competitive with any in the United States. Houston is filled with amenities, including the Texas Medical Center, containing the most advanced hospitals and health care facilities in the world.</p><p ><b>What are some things to do in Houston, Texas?</b></p><p>Houston has a wide variety of cultural and culinary attractions. <a href=\"http://houmuse.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Museum District</a> south of downtown includes the Museum of Natural Science, the Fine Arts Museum, and the Contemporary Arts Museum. The <a href=\"http://www.downtownhouston.org/district/theater/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Theater District</a> contains a number of venues for the performing arts, including concerts at Jones Hall and plays at the Alley Theater. While Houston has a great number of fine and casual dining restaurants, eateries go beyond the standard Tex-Mex and barbecue to include just about every culinary style imaginable.\xA0 Houstonians can cheer on the Astros baseball team, the Rockets basketball team, and the Texans football team. <a href=\"http://www.rodeohouston.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo</a> is an annual event celebrating all things Texan. \xA0Space Center Houston is situated next to NASA's Johnson Space Center, containing numerous static and interactive artifacts of the space program, including a replica of a space shuttle and a Saturn V rocket that took men to the moon. The city is a short drive away from the beaches around Galveston.</p><p ><b>Why you'll love it here</b></p><p>Houston, to sum it up, is a great place to work and play. One can make a career in the city thanks to its robust economy, low cost of living and business-friendly attitude. Houston has enough attractions, from high-brow culture, to popular music that ranges from country, to hip-hop, to food of every type and style, to sports of every kind, to satisfy any taste.\xA0 The best attraction of Houston is its people. Houstonians come from all over the world, but all of them exude that Texas can-do spirit and a friendly sense of neighborliness. A city is not just buildings and roads; it consists of people, as well. Houstonians are some of the friendliest, most self-confident, and hard-working people in the nation.</p>",

With a rich history, thriving local economy and an eclectic mix of residents from all walks of life, Seattle has something to offer every type of homebuyer. Nestled between the breathtaking Puget Sound and the equally beautiful Lake Washington, Seattle is known as an epicenter for food, arts, coffee, music, trade\xA0and much more. An ideal location for those who want to enjoy the diversity and hustle of a larger city, as well as the great outdoors, Seattle offers potential homebuyers\xA0the best of both worlds. With some of the best food, coffee and music in the nation, popular neighborhoods like Capitol Hill, Queen Anne, Ballard and Georgetown each have their own distinct style and diverse demographics that help make Seattle a truly interesting and exciting place to be.\xA0</p><p ><b>What Are Some Things to Do in Seattle?</b></p><p>Seattle offers a great mix of everything from\xA0the arts\xA0to great dining spots, outdoor adventures and a great nightlife scene that attracts visitors from all over the country.         "charleston-sc": "<p id=\"safest\"><b>What's it like to live in Charleston, SC?</b></p><p>Rich with history and definitely not without its southern charm, Charleston is South Carolina's second largest and oldest city. Laid out over about 127 square miles (almost 20 of which are water), the city sits on a peninsula that dips into the Charleston Harbor at the famous Battery and Waterfront Park. Walk through the downtown area where unique shops and famous restaurants flank beautiful, picturesque <a href=\"https://www.movoto.com/blog/homeownership/the-5-best-neighborhoods-in-charleston/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Charleston neighborhoods </a> like South of Broad, Wagener Terrace, Hampton Park Terrace, Cannonborough/Elliotborough, and others. Whether you are a family just starting out, a student at one of the nearby colleges, or a professional working at one of the companies like Google and Boeing that have made Charleston home, there is a place for you in this sweet and sassy southern city.</p><p ><b>What are some things to do in Charleston, SC?</b></p><p>When you make your home in Charleston you'll never be bored. There's no shortage of things to do in Charleston, all you have to do is venture out of your front door. Historic Downtown has a wide variety of quaint shops line the streets, interspersed with world renowned restaurants alternating with undiscovered culinary treasures that only the locals know and frequent. In the middle, you'll find the <a href=\"http://www.thecharlestoncitymarket.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">City Market</a>, a Charleston landmark sprawling over 4 city blocks, housing a diverse collection of merchants from established storefronts to local craftsmen. Waterfront Park with its Pineapple Fountain, as well as the Battery Park draw people to the water's edge. There are piers that take you out over the water for fishing, walking, or just taking in the sights. Park benches and large family-sized swings are place along the shore for relaxing and people watching. The Magnolia Plantations and Gardens, as well as the <a href=\"http://www.scaquarium.org\" rel=\"nofollow\" >South Carolina Aquarium</a> offer family friendly entertainment for enjoying the native (and not so native) wildlife, plant life, and natural wonders. Operated by the <a href=\"http://www.detroitriverfront.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">Detroit Riverfront Conservancy</a>, this area is a 5 \xBD mile waterfront stretch between the Ambassador Bridge and Belle Isle Park. A visit to the Riverfront is one of the most popular things to do in Detroit, and features fountains, green spaces, walking and biking trails, outdoor eateries, sand volleyball courts and even a carousel. Just a short drive from the Riverfront is Detroit's Museum District. Here visitors enjoy the <a href=\"http://www.detroitriverfront.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">Detroit Institute of Arts</a>, which is home to one of the top six art collections in the United States, the Charles H. Wright Museum of African American History, the Detroit Historical Museum and the Michigan Science Center. All within walking distance of each other, it's easy to take in more than one of these attractions in a day. After all of that exploration, visitors can enjoy a show or concert at the Fox Theatre, the Fisher Theatre, the Detroit Opera House or the Max M. Fisher Music Center.</p><p ><b>Why you'll love it here</b><p >Detroit is a city like no other. With deep roots in the lumber industry and its history as the auto capital of the world, Detroit has some of the finest architecture in the country. Architecture enthusiasts appreciate the intricate style of the Guardian Building as well as the work of Albert Khan, who designed both the Fisher Building and the Detroit Athletic Club. Detroit is also home to Motown, meaning\xA0great live music\xA0is always easy to find. And when Detroiters get hungry, a stop at American Coney Island or National Coney Island for a Coney with everything (hot dog with chili, mustard onion), is always a good idea. Because of the city's continued turnaround, it's still possible to find great properties for a fraction of what similar-sized homes would cost in other areas. It's a buyer's market\xA0in the \"D\" but with so much growth and expansion in every part of the city, prices are likely to rise over the next few years.</p>"

      , io = function(e) {
        var t = 1 < arguments.length && void 0 !== arguments[1] ? arguments[1] : []
          , a = {};

            var i = eo[t];

      , oo = {
        methods: {
            generateMapSearchUrl: function(e, t) {
                var a = t.type
                  , i = t.stateCode
                  , o = t.cityName
                  , r = t.zipcode
                  , s = t.neighborhood
                  , n = t.siteMapPropertyPageUrl
                  , l = void 0 === n ? "" : n
                  , d = t.filterArray
                  , c = void 0 === d ? [] : d
                  , p = void 0
                  , h = void 0
                  , u = {
                    base: "",
                    sold: ""
                };
                if (l)
                    p = l.toLowerCase();
                else {
                    switch (a && a.toLowerCase()) {
                    case "city":
                        p = o && i && o.replace(/\s+/g, "-") + "-" + i + "/";
                        break;
                    case "zipcode":
                        p = i && r && i + "/" + r + "/";
                        break;
                    case "neighborhood":
                        p = o && i && s && o.replace(/\s+/g, "-") + "-" + i + "/" + s.replace(/\s+/g, "-") + "/";
                    }
                    p = p && p.toLowerCase()
                }
                return p ? (u.base = u.sold = h = e,
                to(i) ? (h += "for-sale/",
                u.sold += "sold/") : ao(i, o) && a && "city" === a.toLowerCase() && (u.base += "homes-for-sale/"),
                u.base += p,
                h += p,
                u.sold += "" + p + (u.sold.includes("sold") ? "" : "sold/"),
                c && c.length && (u.filteredUrlObj = io(h, c))) : u.filteredUrlObj = {},
                u
            }
        }
    };
